(246, 1, '2018-02-06 05:35:21', '2018-02-06 05:35:21', '<div class=\"container\">\r\n<div class=\"row row-bg-design\">\r\n<div class=\"col-sm-8\">\r\n<h3>Motivo Dental in Edmonton West</h3>\r\n<p class=\"call-inner\">Call (780)757-1900 to book an appointment!</p>\r\nAt Motivo Dental in Edmonton West,  we try to satisfy our patients dental requirements in the most comfortable way with minimal pain\r\nEvery individual is unique, so we believe that our treatment approach should be tailored to accommodate each patient’s needs.\r\n<h3>To achieve this, Motivo Dental in Edmonton West provides the following:</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"about-us-listing\">\r\n 	<li>Relaxing environment and pleasing design.</li>\r\n 	<li>We spend the necessary time with each patient, nothing is done in a hurry, we make sure all patient questions are answered in the proper way.</li>\r\n 	<li>We focus on prevention and patient education, we make sure that every patient masters oral hygiene techniques so the dental decay is reduced to the minimum.</li>\r\n 	<li>High Technology equipment, Motivo Dental is fully digital, and we use 3- dimensional X-ray if needed, especially for dental implants cases and root canal treatments.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-sm-4 image-design\"><div class=\"inner-page-outer-img\"><img src=\"http://webdevelopers1.com/motivodental/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/about-us-small.jpg\" /></div></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"row row-bg-design\">\r\n<div class=\"col-sm-12\">\r\n<p class=\"about-us-iframe\"><iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/jkwVXM2ZIeQ\" width=\"300\" height=\"150\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'Who We Are', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '245-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-02-06 05:35:21', '2018-02-06 05:35:21', '', 245, 'http://webdevelopers1.com/motivodental/245-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(247, 1, '2018-02-06 05:40:08', '2018-02-06 05:40:08', '<div class=\"\">\r\n<div class=\"row row-bg-design\">\r\n<div class=\"col-sm-8\">\r\n<h3> Dr Khaled Alhomsi </h3>\r\nGeneral Dentist\r\n Dr Alhomsi has been practicing dentistry since 1997, he is a general dentist and provides full dental service. His passion to dentistry and love for his patients have led him to follow advanced training in most branches of dentistry. Dr Alhomsi worked in Spruce Grove, St Albert, and now provides dental care at Motivo Dental in West Edmonton.\r\n<h3>Dentist in West Edmonton</h3>\r\n<p class=\"call-inner\"><a href=\"callto:(780)757-1900\">Call </a>(780)757-1900 to book an appointment!</p>\r\n\r\nDr. Alhomsi graduated from high school in 1992 with distinction, and chose to become a dentist because it enabled him to combine several of his interests -arts, science, and entrepreneurship- and direct them towards providing a valuable human service.\r\n\r\nAfter graduating as a dentist from Damascus University in 1997, Dr Alhomsi worked as a general dentist in the public hospitals in Damascus- Syria for two years, he also opened his own private dental office in Damascus in 1998. He practiced all branches of dentistry, and saw thousands of patients with all dental problems, he excelled in oral surgery and endodontics and had great success as a general practitioner.\r\n\r\nIn 2000, Dr Alhomsi pursued  postgraduate training in orthodontics in France, he had his Certificate d’ in orthodontics and dento-facial orthopedics from the University of Lyon- France by the end of 2002, which enabled him to become a specialist in orthodontics in Syria.\r\n\r\nFrom 2003 to 2009, Dr Alhomsi practiced orthodontics in his private office in Damascus, but he didn’t limit his practice to orthodontics, he also provided all kind of cosmetic dentistry, including complete oral rehabilitation, smile makeovers, and gingival cosmetic surgery and grafts, he had the Certificat d’Etudes Superieures in fixed dental prosthodontics from the university of Lyon in 2005.\r\n\r\nThriving for freedom and the western quality of life, Dr Alhomsi moved to Canada with his family to settle down in Montreal in 2009, there he had to go to the dental school again to be able to work as a dentist in Canada, he took that challenge and was admitted to the University of Montreal- faculty of dental medicine- in 2010, he graduated with DMD degree in June 2013.\r\nSoon after graduation, Dr Alhomsi moved to St Albert – Alberta, to start practicing dentistry again.\r\n\r\nHe has been working with Smiles Dental Group since then, and practicing all branches of dentistry again.\r\n\r\nDr Alhomsi provides full dental service.  He is certified in implant dentistry from the Misch Institute in Toronto, and also certified in conscious sedation from the University of Alberta.\r\n\r\nIn his practice, Dr Alhomsi maintains a great relation with his patients.  His production as a dentist is high – thanks to his ability to perform almost any type of dental treatment with a very high standard.  Also, besides English, Dr. Alhomsi also speaks fluent French.\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-sm-4 image-design\"><div class=\"inner-page-outer-img\"><img src=\"http://webdevelopers1.com/motivodental/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/about-us-small.jpg\" /></div></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"row row-bg-design\">\r\n<div class=\"col-sm-12\">\r\n<p class=\"about-us-iframe\">\r\n<iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/V1Dv8kbZICo\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\" width=\"300\" height=\"150\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'Doctors', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'doctors', '', '', '2018-02-20 07:44:57', '2018-02-20 07:44:57', '', 0, 'http://webdevelopers1.com/motivodental/?page_id=247', 0, 'page', '', 0),
