(344, 1, '2018-02-14 06:56:04', '2018-02-14 06:56:04', '<div class=\"\">\n<div class=\"row row-bg-design\">\n<div class=\"col-sm-8\">\n<p class=\"call-inner\">Call <a href=\"callto:(780)757-1900\">(780)757-1900</a> !</p>\n\n<h3>Sedation Dentistry</h3>\n<ul class=\"about-us-listing\">\n 	<li>At Motivo Dental in West Edmonton we provide conscious sedation to our patients if required.</li>\n 	<li>Fear of dentistry is real and pretty common, it is estimated that between 6% and 14% of the population try to avoid dental treatment or even dental check- ups because of this fear; that can lead to serious dental problems as those patients only go to see the dentist when serious pain happens.</li>\n 	<li>Conscious sedation can decrease patient’s anxiety and can help people who have dentistry phobia to overcome their fears and have a good experience with their dental treatment.</li>\n<li>Conscious sedation is a minimally depressed level of consciousness that retains the patient’s ability to independently and continuously maintain an airway and respond appropriately to physical stimulation and verbal commands.</li>\n<li>At Motivo Dental in West Edmonton we achieve conscious sedation by using the laughing gas, sedation pills, or both.</li>\n<li></li>\n<li></li>\n<li></li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;\n\nIf your gums do hurt or bleed while brushing or flossing, or you are experiencing persistent bad breath, see your dentist. Any of these conditions may indicate a problem.\n\nYour dentist or hygienist can help you learn good oral hygiene techniques and can help point out areas of your mouth that may require extra attention during brushing and flossing.\n\n</div>\n<div class=\"col-sm-4 image-design\">\n<div class=\"inner-page-outer-img\"><img src=\"http://webdevelopers1.com/motivodental/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/sedation.jpg\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"row row-bg-design\">\n<div class=\"col-sm-12\">\n<p class=\"about-us-iframe\"><iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/V1Dv8kbZIC