(335, 1, '2018-03-05 10:00:12', '2018-03-05 10:00:12', '<div class=\"row row-bg-design\">\n<div class=\"col-sm-8\">\n<p class=\"call-inner\">Call <a href=\"callto:(780)757-1900\">(780)757-1900</a> to book an appointment!</p>\n\n<h3>Invisalign/ Invisible Braces in Edmonton</h3>\nInvisalign is a technique used to align crooked teeth and correct bad bites (malocclusion). It is commonly used for adult orthodontics and for people who don’t want the look of braces but want beautiful smiles.\nDr Alhomsi at Motivo Dental is a registered Invisalign provider.\n<h3>WHAT IS INVISALIGN?</h3>\nnvisalign consists of making transparent, almost invisible trays that are custom-made for each patient. They are made of smooth plastic that is compatible with the oral environment. These trays are clear and fit your teeth perfectly, when you have treatment with invisalign you get a set of trays and you need to change the tray every 10-14 days.\n<h3>HOW DOES INVISALIGN WORK?</h3>\nInvisalign applies a gentle force on your teeth, so they move slowly in the desired direction. The movement of the teeth is simulated on a software, and the invisalign trays are manufactured according to this software. Each tray will move your teeth a bit, and then you have to use the next tray in the series until the treatment goal is reached.\n<h3>HOW LONG IT TAKES TO FINISH INVISALIGN TREATMENT?</h3>\nThe length of the treatment really depends on the severity of the case. As mentioned above, each invisalign tray will move the teeth a bit, so small cases will be finished faster than complicated cases. Usually the invisalign treatment will take between few months to one or two years.\n<h3>WHAT IS THE ADVANTAGE OF USING INVISALIGN OVER BRACES?</h3>\nAesthetics: Invisalign is almost invisible. People usually cannot see that you are wearing the invisalign tray, which makes Invisalign more cosmetic than using the traditional braces.\n\nComfort: Invisalign trays fit your teeth perfectly. They are smooth so they don’t hurt your tongue, lips, or cheeks, and they don’t affect your speech. They don’t affect your eating either because you are required to take them out of your mouth when you eat. \nHygiene: Invislaign trays are removable, so you take them out when you eat, and no food will stick on them as what happens with traditional or lingual (invisible) braces. On the other hand, you can brush and floss your teeth as usual without the need for a special brushing technique as you may need when traditional braces are used.\n\nComfort: Invisalign trays fit your teeth perfectly, they are smooth so they don’t hurt your tongue, lips, or cheeks, they don’t\naffect your speech, they don’t affect your eating neither because you take them out of your mouth when you eat.\nthis makes Invisalign superior to Invisible braces that may be invisible but so much uncomfortable.\n\nHygiene: Invislaign trays are removable, so you take them out when you eat, and no food will stick on them as what happens with\ntraditional or lingual(invisible) braces. On the other hand, you can brush and floss your teeth as usual without the need for\na special brushing technique as you may need when traditional braces are used.\n<h3>INVISALIGN LIMITS:</h3>\nAfter the above mentioned advantages of Invisalign, why don’t we use Invisalign for all orthodontic cases? Why do we still use Braces? Unfortunately Invisalign cannot be used for all cases of malocclusion, and many cases still need Braces. Your dentist/ orthodontist will tell you if Invisalign is good for you.\n<h3>INVISALIGN PROCEDURE:</h3>\nAfter the above mentioned advantages of Invisalign, why don’t we use Invisalign for all orthodontic cases? Why do we still use Braces? Unfortunately Invisalign cannot be used for all cases of malocclusion, and many cases still need Braces. Your dentist/ orthodontist will tell you if Invisalign is good for you.\nFirst you need to have a consultation with the dentist, then the dentist will take the necessary pictures and x-rays.\n\nThe second step is to creat a stimulation of the treatment on a software called the Clincheck, this enables the dentist to show\nyou how your teeth will move and the approximate outcome of the treatment.\nIf you are happy with that outcome, the trays will be manufactured.\nabout 1-2 weeks later we will insert the first tray , and will give you the instructions how to use them.\n\nYou need to see the come and see us every 8 weeks so we can verify the treatment progress and do any necessary adjustment.\n<h3>WHY SHOULD YOU TREAT CROOKED TEETH AND MALOCCLUSION?</h3>\nCrooked teeth are not pleasant to look at, but they may also cause more troubles than cosmetics:\nmal-aligned teeth are hard to brush and floss, this can lead to food accumulation between the teeth, which leads to\ndental cavities, bad mouth breath, and gum inflammation.\ncrooked teeth may also cause a bad bite, bad bites can cause damage to the teeth, the gum, the bone,the muscles, and the temporomandibular\njoints.\n\n</div>\n<div class=\"col-sm-4 image-design\">\n<div class=\"inner-page-outer-img\"><img src=\"http://webdevelopers1.com/motivodental/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/invisalign-1.jpg\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"row row-bg-design\">\n<div class=\"col-sm-12\">\n<p class=\"about-us-iframe\"><iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/jkwVXM2ZIeQ\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\n\n<div>Motivo Dental provides dental services like <a href=\"http://webdevelopers1.com/motivodental/emergency/\">emergency dental service</a>, <a href=\"http://webdevelopers1.com/motivodental/services/dental-implants/\">dental implants</a>, <a href=\"http://webdevelopers1.com/motivodental/services/braces-orthodontics/\">orthodontics</a>, <a href=\"http://webdevelopers1.com/motivodental/services/invisalign-invisible-braces/\">invsialign</a>, <a href=\"http://webdevelopers1.com/motivodental/services/dental-bridges/\">dental bridge</a>, <a href=\"http://webdevelopers1.com/motivodental/services/dental-crowns/\">dental crowns</a>, <a href=\"http://webdevelopers1.com/motivodental/services/teeth-whitening/\">teeth whitening</a> etc.</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Invisalign/ Invisible Braces', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '331-autosave-v1', '', '', '2018-03-05 10:00:12', '2018-03-05 10:00:12', '', 331, 'http://webdevelopers1.com/motivodental/331-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
